/// kotoba:kge — Kotoba Game Engine WIT contract (ADR-2606060001)
///
/// The deterministic per-tick simulation contract. The SAME compiled component
/// runs as server authority AND as browser client prediction (kotoba-runtime-web).
///
/// DETERMINISM IS LOAD-BEARING. A `kge` world deliberately imports NOTHING that
/// could make `step` nondeterministic — no `wasi:clocks`, no random, no sockets,
/// and none of the `kotoba:kais` foreign bridges (`llm`/`evm`/`btc`/`chain`).
/// Nondeterminism is removed by construction, not by documentation.
///
/// Drive model: the GUEST EXPORTS the simulation; the HOST (kotoba-rt `WasmSim`)
/// owns the loop and calls `step`/`snapshot`/`state-hash`. This is the inverse of
/// a typical host-capability world — here the host is the rollback engine.
///
/// Host mapping (kotoba-runtime / kotoba-runtime-web binding):
///   - the host snapshots/restores the guest's LINEAR MEMORY directly for the
///     per-frame rollback save (fast path) — it does NOT call `snapshot` per
///     frame. `snapshot`/`restore` are the SLOW, canonical, content-addressed
///     path used for the cold-lane commit / replay / resync only.
package kotoba:kge@0.1.0;

interface kge {
    /// One player's input for one tick. `axes` are quantized on ingest; the
    /// canonical state that feeds `state-hash` must be integer/fixed-point.
    record input {
        player:  u32,
        buttons: u32,
        axes:    list<f32>,
    }

    /// Deterministic initialization from a shared seed + match config.
    init: func(seed: u64, config: list<u8>) -> result<_, string>;

    /// Advance EXACTLY one tick. MUST be a pure function of
    /// (previous-state, inputs). No wall-clock, no host RNG, no I/O.
    step: func(tick: u64, inputs: list<input>) -> result<_, string>;

    /// DURABLE snapshot (slow path): canonical, serialized, content-addressable
    /// blob for the cold lane (commit / replay / resume).
    snapshot: func() -> result<list<u8>, string>;
    restore:  func(blob: list<u8>) -> result<_, string>;

    /// Desync DETECTOR (not a reconciler): canonical state hash compared across
    /// peers each confirmed tick. Mismatch ⇒ resync by snapshot CID.
    state-hash: func() -> result<list<u8>, string>;
}

/// The restricted world a game component targets. Note what is ABSENT: no
/// `wasi:clocks`, no random, no sockets, and none of the `kotoba:kais` foreign
/// bridges — nondeterminism is uninstantiable, not merely discouraged.
world game {
    export kge;
}
